Here’s how you know

Official websites use .gov
A .gov website belongs to an official government organization in the United States.

Secure .gov websites use HTTPS
A lock ( ) or https:// means you’ve safely connected to the .gov website. Share sensitive information only on official, secure websites.

What we deliver

Strategies and services that help agencies provide excellent value to the public.

18F partners with federal agencies to improve the user experience of government services by helping them build and buy technology. If you're looking to implement a requirement, update a public-facing website, or digitize a process, 18F can work with you to build a product or craft and execute an effective agile acquisition strategy.

Case Studies

  • U.S. Forest Service

    Moving land permits online

    Using prototypes and modular contracting to help the Forest Service buy and develop an online permitting system.

    Read more about Moving land permits online
  • Alaska Department of Health and Social Services

    Modernizing access to healthcare

    Introducing modern digital methods to the State of Alaska’s eligibility system modernization project.

    Read more about Modernizing access to healthcare
  • Department of Justice

    Improving access to justice through a user-friendly online submission experience

    Developing a user-friendly online submission experience for the civil rights complaint portal

    Read more about Improving access to justice through a user-friendly online submission experience
  • U.S. Tax Court

    Making it easier to resolve tax disputes

    Developing a new petition and document-filing experience for taxpayers without lawyers, and a better case management workflow for Tax Court employees

    Read more about Making it easier to resolve tax disputes
  • Department of the Treasury

    Implementing a government-wide law

    Implementing the Digital Accountability and Transparency Act with one of the largest government-wide agile projects ever undertaken.

    Read more about Implementing a government-wide law
  • Department of State

    Fitting our analysis to your challenge

    Leveraging our technical expertise with USKPA's program knowledge to improve the tracking of rough diamonds

    Read more about Fitting our analysis to your challenge
“18F’s philosophy to build everything openly by default has been a key success factor in our ability to build credibility with the external stakeholders who have been critical of us previously. More importantly, this way of building facilitates innovation in an eco-centric manner as opposed to just within the government or a few entities.”

— Christina Ho
Former Deputy Assistant Secretary, Office of Accounting Policy & Financial Transparency, Department of the Treasury
